The paper discusses the use of neural network models for natural language processing tasks, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the advantages of using neural networks for feature extraction, which is a topic of interest in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of non-local features, which is a topic of interest in neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CV.
